name: Cardiovascular System
description: The body system responsible for circulating blood, transporting oxygen and nutrients.

name: Musculoskeletal System
description: The body system composed of bones, muscles, ligaments, tendons, and joints, providing structure and movement.

name: Respiratory System
description: The body system responsible for gas exchange, taking in oxygen and expelling carbon dioxide.

name: Nervous System
description: The body system that coordinates actions and transmits signals between different parts of the body.

name: Digestive System
description: The body system responsible for breaking down food, absorbing nutrients, and eliminating waste.

name: Endocrine System
description: The body system of glands that produce hormones regulating metabolism, growth, tissue function, etc.

name: Urinary System
description: The body system that filters blood and eliminates waste in the form of urine.

name: Integumentary System
description: The body system consisting of the skin, hair, nails, and exocrine glands, protecting the body.
